(2) The Board may— (a) accept money by way of grants or donations or in any other form from any source and invest it in such manner as the Board considers fit: Provided that the Board shall not receive any grant or donation, unless it approves of the purpose to which the grant or donation shall be applied and the conditions, if any, under which the grant or donation is made; (b) raise by way of loans, or otherwise, from any source within Zambia, and subject to the approval of the Minister, from any source outside Zambia, such monies as it may require for the discharge of its functions; (c) charge and collect fees in respect of programmes, publications, seminars, consultancy services and other services provided by the Board ; and (d) charge fees for courses, seminars and workshops.
